[4] Pakistan (Sindh)
Date: Fri 30 Nov 2012
Source: The International News [edited]
http://www.thenews.com.pk/Todays-News-2-145746-WHO-team-rushes-to-Khairpur-to-probe-deaths-due-to-measles


A team from the World Health Organisation (WHO) rushed on Wednesday [28 Nov 2012] to investigate the reasons for an outbreak of [measles] in the town of Thari Mirwah in Khairpur [district].

The WHO Surveillance Officer, Dr Asad Soomro, along with DHO [Department of Health officer] Khairpur and other health officials, reached Aajb Khan Dasti and other villages [around] Thari Mirwah town, where 8 children had died of measles.

During its visit to other villages, the team found that most of the villagers had not gotten their children vaccinated against measles. The team also found that the disease developed into pneumonia, which resulted in deaths of the children. Investigation also revealed that the parents, instead of taking their children to health centres, took them for cure to Hindu spiritual men.

The team found that there were 98 measles cases in Khairpur town, 95 in Kingri, 38 in Kotdiji, 121 in Gambat, 19 in Nara, 41 in Thari Mirwah town, and 18 in Faiz Gunj Town. The team said 17 children, including 9 in Thari Mirwah, 6 in Gambat and 2 in Kingri Taluka had died of measles.

--
